message.content:
A Bombus auricomus is a species of bumblebee.
It has a fuzzy black body with vibrant yellow stripes and a rusty orange patch on the thorax.
Its wings are transparent and relatively short compared to its body size.
They have two pairs of legs covered with black, long hairs.
Bombus auricomus can commonly be found in North America and parts of Europe.
They are known for their important role in pollinating various plants.
This bee species is crucial for the proper functioning of ecosystems and agricultural production.
